Groppi mocker/Groppi mokka
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:dress clothes; dress uniform; a dinner suit. (from Groppi's, a Cairo restaurant)
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (WW2 Egypt) Note also: A dinner jacket [?a mishearing or transformation: P.Munz was not certain] ca1975 p.c. Professor Peter Munz misheard the expression (for `dinner suit') as used by John O'Shea (Wellington)  ....to put on a smokey gropper.
