Date:  4/10/1982
Source:  Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page:  41
Edition:
Quote:  The Groppi tea shop in the heart of the commercial centre [of Cairo] still does a thriving business, selling tea and ice cream to middle class Egyptians and occasional tourists.

The tea house fashionable even during the war, insinuated itself into the language with `groppi mocka' being the best clothes the Kiwis could muster for a day on the town.
